https://vrcommunityawards.com/ --><!--Are you able to follow up with this? Please and thank you. ~DAG 02/15/2025 -->The '''VR Community Awards (VRCA)''' is a community-made awards ceremony to acknowledge achievements of the VR Community, primarily VRChat. Hosted, and established in 2024, by VRCPuck<!-- Unsure whether or not to add a link here --><!--I do not think we should add a link for content creators, however I added a link for VRCA's official website ~DAG 02/15/25 -->.

The awards feature 35 categories ranging from [[Avatars|avatar]] creators, VR DJs, large communities, dancers, VR photographers, and more. The show works in association with VKet, Projekt: Community, Local Police Department, Gamer Supps, [[Community:Trans Academy|Trans Academy]], Blerp, and [[Community:VRDancing|VRDancing]].

VRChat's account on Bluesky created a post<ref>[https://vrcommunityawards.com/ 'The VR Community Awards 2024 Are Open NOW! Vote for Your Favorite Creators and Communities on VRChat'], posted by VRChat on ''Bluesky'', December 1st, 2024; retrieved December 26, 2024.</ref> announcing the VRCAs on December 1st, 2024. The winners for VR Community Awards 2024 were announced on February 16, 2025.

==Voting==
Voting could be done online through the VR Community Awards [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uLXr3lIHozM website], where users could vote the winner for any nominees in any of the thirty-five categories. VRChat also sponsored the voting process for the VR Community Awards through a Launch Pad (IPS) banner on the [[Quick Menu]].

